<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="906" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 417.00/43.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-01"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Does the wording “by the present Nicaraguan Government,” in article 6,
                            apply to the Government of President Estrada? The Nicaraguan Government
                            fears this paragraph would require reinstatement of the concession of
                            the Bluefields Steamship Co., with its exclusive right of navigating
                            Escondido River, of the lottery concession, and of other concessions
                            referred to in the ministers dispatch 52, of May 25.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>